            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EMoney%20tests%20our%20hearts%2C%20our%20motives%2C%20and%20our%20character.%20What%20we%20do%20with%20it%20will%20prove%20to%20God%20whether%20He%20can%20entrust%20us%20with%20the%20%22true%20riches%20of%20heaven%22%20spoken%20of%20in%20Luke%2016%3A11.%20The%20spirit%20of%20covetousness%20ruled%20the%20Pharisees.%20The%20Lord%20warned%20them%20that%20they%20could%20not%20%22serve%20both%20God%20and%20money%22%20(v.%2013)%2C%20but%20verse%2014%20says%20they%20%22dearly%20loved%20their%20money%2C%22%20ignoring%20the%20Lord's%20stern%20admonition%20to%20them.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20principle%20of%20covetousness%20is%20immortalized%20in%20the%20story%20of%20Achan%20in%20the%20Old%20Testament.%20God%20gave%20explicit%20instructions%20to%20Joshua%20that%20no%20one%20was%20to%20touch%20anything%20of%20value%20in%20Jericho.%20The%20entire%20city%20was%20God's%2C%20dedicated%20to%20Him%20as%20the%20holy%20firstfruits%20of%20the%20Canaan%20conquest.%20Achan's%20hand%2C%20however%2C%20could%20not%20resist%20grasping%20a%20bar%20of%20gold%2C%20coins%20of%20silver%2C%20and%20a%20beautiful%20Babylonian%20coat.%20His%20sin%20followed%20a%20familiar%20pattern%3A%20%22I%20saw%20.%20.%20.%20I%20wanted%20.%20.%20.%20I%20took%20them%20.%20.%20.%20They%20are%20hidden%22%20(Joshua%207%3A21).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOur%20eyes%20can%20look%20enviously%20on%20things%20that%20do%20not%20belong%20to%20us%2C%20and%20covetousness%20can%20lead%20us%20to%20%22take%22%20and%20%22hide%22%20that%20which%20is%20not%20ours.%20How%20much%20better%20to%20follow%20the%20wisdom%20of%20Luke%2016%3A9%3A%20%22I%20tell%20you%2C%20use%20your%20worldly%20resources%20to%20benefit%20others%20and%20make%20friends.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20your%20generosity%20stores%20up%20a%20reward%20for%20you%20in%20heaven.%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EUse%20worldly%20wealth%3B%20don't%20let%20it%20use%20you!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
